    "url": "https://www.ibm.com/think/topics/artificial-intelligence",
    "content": "Directly underneath AI, we have machine learning, which involves creating models by training an algorithm to make predictions or decisions based on data. Generative AI, sometimes called \"gen AI\", refers to deep learning models that can create complex original content\u2014such as long-form text, high-quality images, realistic video or audio and more\u2014in response to a user\u2019s prompt or request. Another option for improving a gen AI app's performance is retrieval augmented generation (RAG), a technique for extending the foundation model to use relevant sources outside of the training data to refine the parameters for greater accuracy or relevance. With these new generative AI practices, deep-learning models can be pretrained on large amounts of data. Train, validate, tune and deploy generative AI, foundation models and machine learning capabilities with IBM watsonx.ai, a next-generation enterprise studio for AI builders."
